AB  - We report a case of Crohn's disease with low serum zinc concentration in a
      26-year-old woman. She demonstrated acrodermatitis enteropathica and decreased
      visual acuity during total parenteral nutrition. Subsequent intravenous zinc
      supplementation resulted in alleviation of the skin lesions and improvement of
      visual acuity. This case supports the notion that depressed serum zinc in Crohn's
