TI  - Skin content of 7-dehydrocholesterol in patients with malabsorption.
PG  - 771-3
AB  - The mechanism for the development of vitamin D deficiency in patients with
      malabsorption remains unclear. We wished to examine the hypothesis that one
      factor was a reduced skin content of 7-dehydrocholesterol, the precursor for the 
      formation of vitamin D in the presence of ultraviolet radiation. We measured
      7-dehydrocholesterol in skin samples from 9 patients who had previously had
      vitamin D deficiency due to malabsorption (6 with Crohn's disease, 2 with primary
      biliary cirrhosis, and 1 with idiopathic pseudo-obstruction). We found no
      evidence of reduced levels of 7-dehydrocholesterol in the skin in these patients.
      Lack of 7-dehydrocholesterol does not contribute to vitamin D deficiency in
      malabsorption.
